description: The strategy devised by scientists was to keep large parts of society open but not everyone is convinced.
title: Coronavirus: Has Sweden got its science right?
title_page: Coronavirus: Has Sweden got its science right? - BBC News
maintext: "When it comes to studies and other types of coronaviruses, they have shown that people get immune. Maybe not long-term immunity, but even if we only get this kind of short-term immunity, it may be enough to stop this pandemic," says Dr Frans.
